Hi AllState,
 
Thank you for reaching out to Netwrix Technical Support. We want to assure you that your inquiry is a top priority and we are fully committed to resolving your issue.
 
Was it working before?
If it was working before and stopped, when did it stop?
 
We need to schedule a meeting to review the setting and better understand the issue. Before the meeting, ensure the job is set to Debug and rerun the job to collect the log.
 
To set the job to Debug, expand Settings, click Application, and under Application log, click the drop-down, select DEBUG, and click Save at the right lower corner of the screen to save changes.
 
You can use the link below to schedule the meeting.

On review of the error messages it looks like the service account for Sharepoint Online doesn't have access to certain resources.

	When did it start to happen?
	Is this a new set of resources in the SPAA scope or the scan is failing for already specified resources?

Best regards,

TextBody:
ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000C53G5:ref

Hi Aleksandr,

To answer your questions

  1.  When did it start to happen?

We are only recently seeing this happen as the SP job had not been running due to an internal remediation process that has now completed.

  1.  Is this a new set of resources in the SPAA scope or the scan is failing for already specified resources?
There are additional resources in the SPAA scope that we did not originally scan but moving forward we will be scanning (ie: Teams)
These new resources are failing however we are getting other fails for specified resources.
We are not pulling back any data for the whole tenant (allstate cloud)

  1.  Can you verify the service account has access to the resources in the error messages?
SP team has verified that the service account does have access to scan the tenant (allstate cloud)

  1.  Can you share the SPAA System Scan job logs for investigation?
I have uploaded the job log to the ticket.

I have spoken to the SP team who have looked at the error messages , they informed me that we are able to connect to the tenant and can hit the site but have issues with the site assets. They believed that you may be able to help resolve the issue upon investigation as they don’t know why we are getting these errors.
They had also provided me with 2 specific sites to test against but both showed offline in Stealthaudit which SP team say are not offline.
I plan to talk again with the SP team today and I am currently rerunning the job.

Can we please schedule a call to discuss these issues.

Many Thanks
Nuala

Hi Aleksandr,

 

To answer your questions


	When did it start to happen?


We are only recently seeing this happen as the SP job had not been running due to an internal remediation process that has now completed.


	Is this a new set of resources in the SPAA scope or the scan is failing for already specified resources?


There are additional resources in the SPAA scope that we did not originally scan but moving forward we will be scanning (ie: Teams)

These new resources are failing however we are getting other fails for specified resources. 

We are not pulling back any data for the whole tenant (allstate cloud) 


	Can you verify the service account has access to the resources in the error messages?


SP team has verified that the service account does have access to scan the tenant (allstate cloud)


	Can you share the SPAA System Scan job logs for investigation?


I have uploaded the job log to the ticket. 

 

I have spoken to the SP team who have looked at the error messages , they informed me that we are able to connect to the tenant and can hit the site but have issues with the site assets. They believed that you may be able to help resolve the issue upon investigation as they don’t know why we are getting these errors.

They had also provided me with 2 specific sites to test against but both showed offline in Stealthaudit which SP team say are not offline.

I plan to talk again with the SP team today and I am currently rerunning the job.

 

Can we please schedule a call to discuss these issues.

 

Many Thanks

Nuala
